					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I just thought about this - forgive me if its been brought up before. I mean, Nintendo is going to make a virtual console which is going to play NES, SNES, GB, N64, SEGA, and arcade games. Doesn't that like...suck? I mean think of all those emulators they have to make. Having made an NES and GB emulator that's far from perfect, I know how difficult it can be. Is it that much easier to make emulators for dedicated consoles? Is having access to direct tech specs gonna make it a piece of cake? Maybe they only care about getting specific games working, but I know some NES games are a PAIN to get right without some crazy detail.</div>

