						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">blargg wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">* Nintendo has full authoritative NES documentation and likely many of the original programmers who knew the machine intimately.</div>
<br />
<br />Also, they are making their own custom chips.  Given that they have the original designs, it's not that hard to drop a 6502 and a NES PPU macro into the design, and it would take a very small number of gates.  That would give them a hardware implementation of the console in question.  I doubt they would bother with this on the NES, but I wouldn't be too surprised if there was some extra harware acceleration to handle things like the vector processor in the N64.</div>

